DOCS.GOOGLE.COM
Meal Program Sign Up Form - Hybrid

Ogilvie Elementary
September 10 at 8:43 AM ·

GREAT news, Ogilvie Public Schools Families!!!

The US Dept. of Agriculture (USDA) and Minnesota Department of Education (MDE) just released this last Friday - the extension of our Ogilvie Summer Food Program through December 31st, or ending sooner if the funds become depleted.

This means breakfast and lunch for ALL children ages 1 through 18 at absolutely no cost to our families!

Yes--FREE MEALS for all children!

While your children/our students are at school - they will automatically receive these free meals, if you choose to participate.

If there are ANY OTHER CHILDREN in the community (not school-age yet) that you'd like to receive free meals for, please contact our Food Service Department at 320-272-5020. We ask that those ordered meals be picked up daily between 10:30 and 1:00.

For Distance Learning Students and Families, you will be contacted by the district for your meal planning.

For 7-12 Students in Hybrid Learning, please complete the following survey for meals:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSe2ZJRuIGUvCY12ECzjz9eA3mwSIqDLEGlvxn1HGC0Yp-9Kdw/viewform

post_text:
Ogilvie Public Schools is in the process of planning for the 2020-2021 school year. A task team met today and is following the MN Department of Education requirements as they develop 3 education plans for the upcoming school year. The plan options are:
1. Continue with Distance Learning.
2. All staff and students back in the building.
3. A hybrid model using 50% capacity of the building for student learning each day.

Please stay tuned as we plan for the best learning experience for your children in accordance with MDE, MDH, and CDC guidelines!

IMPORTANT: MDE has extended the deadline to July 31st for families to apply for P-EBT (Pandemic Electronic Benefits). This additional benefit is for families who qualify for the Free & Reduced program. Families will receive $325 per school aged child. If you have any questions, please call the school.

DRIVER'S ED CLASSROOM TRAINING

Ogilvie Schools, in conjunction with Mike Anson of the A-Z Driver’s Instruction, are offering classroom driver’s training instruction for the convenience of our students and their families.

Due to building restrictions, our Driver's Ed class will be held at A-Z Driving Instruction in Milaca. The classroom instruction is 10 consecutive days including Mondays (August 10,11,12,13,14,17,18,19,20 & 21) from 1:00-4:00 p.m. The total cost for this classroom instruction is $150 - $20 to Ogilvie Schools and $130 to A-Z Driver’s Instruction. (Two separate checks, please.) This is due by the first day of class (Aug 10).

Behind the wheel training is $300. This is not due until they start behind the wheel training.

Please register by Friday July 31, 2020 on https://bit.ly/ocedriversed.

text: Class of 2020 graduation ceremony will be starting in a few minutes on our OPS Live Facebook page!

post_text:
PRESCHOOL GRADUATION
The end of May is a time when the Ogilvie community eagerly awaits two graduation ceremonies! First, the community packs Ogilvie’s auditorium to celebrate the Preschool 4 Class graduates. Then, they pack the gymnasium to celebrate the Senior Class. This May, however, programs, celebrations, and pomp and circumstance needed to look a bit different from the past. On Thursday, May 28th Preschool families participated in a Drive-Up Graduation ceremony instead of the traditional program. Preschool graduates were greeted in Ogilvie’s parking lot by smiling and excited Preschool Staff, music, and congratulations posters. Students were given their PreK grad hats, certificates, scrapbooks, graduation t-shirts, and a few other special memories from the year. Families were able to have a drive-up photo taken with a graduation banner and PreK grads were wished by staff a fun summer and many more congrats as they drove through the parking lot.

Thank you, families, for choosing Ogilvie Preschool this year and best wishes from Ogilvie Preschool Staff!
text:
PRESCHOOL GRADUATION
The end of May is a time when the Ogilvie community eagerly awaits two graduation ceremonies! First, the community packs Ogilvie’s auditorium to celebrate the Preschool 4 Class graduates. Then, they pack the gymnasium to celebrate the Senior Class. This May, however, programs, celebrations, and pomp and circumstance needed to look a bit different from the past. On Thursday, May 28th Preschool families participated in a Drive-Up Graduation ceremony instead of the traditional program. Preschool graduates were greeted in Ogilvie’s parking lot by smiling and excited Preschool Staff, music, and congratulations posters. Students were given their PreK grad hats, certificates, scrapbooks, graduation t-shirts, and a few other special memories from the year. Families were able to have a drive-up photo taken with a graduation banner and PreK grads were wished by staff a fun summer and many more congrats as they drove through the parking lot.

Thank you, families, for choosing Ogilvie Preschool this year and best wishes from Ogilvie Preschool Staff!

Ogilvie High School celebrated our seniors today by having a "senior drive-thru" where they were given bags filled with gifts, candy, awards and more! The videos from this event can be found on our "OPS Live" Facebook account.
For a couple seniors unable to make it, staff decided to load up in a bus and bring the gifts and recognition to them!
Congratulations to all our seniors as they will soon receive their diplomas!

Ogilvie Public Schools is once again offering a summer meal program for ALL children ages 1-18. Children are not required to live within the district.
You only need to sign up ONCE for the summer program and meals will be prepared for you each week. To start receiving meals on Tuesday, you need to have been signed up by the previous Friday.

PICKUP DATES: June 2, 9, 16. July 7, 14, 21, 28. August 11, 18, 25.
PICKUP TIME: 2:00 - 6:00 pm
Please notify the school if you aren't available to pickup your meals on any of the scheduled dates.

Ogilvie School District Yearbook
May 12 at 8:55 PM ·

All the people who ordered yearbooks will still be receiving them. Due to COVID, the Balfour printing plant has been closed since the beginning of April. They are scheduled to open the end of this week. However, in a typical year, it's about 6 weeks for the process until we have them delivered at our school. So we know it'll be sometime during the summer when the yearbooks arrive. At this time, we are planning for a curbside pickup to distribute them or to at least start the process of getting them out to those who ordered.

post_text:
A message from Superintendent Belsheim regarding the 4-day school week...

The Minnesota Department of Education has informed all 4-Day School Week Districts that they have been granted an extension through the 2020-2021 school year to continue 4-Day Education.

The Ogilvie School Board will be discussing our 4-Day structure at their school board meeting tomorrow night (January 13th). The meeting is at 6:00 p.m. You are invited to attend and share your perspective with the board - or just to listen to the open discussion.

The Ogilvie School Board will be taking action at their January 27th meeting to either continue with 4-Day instruction for the 2020-21 school year, or to return to a 5-Day structure.

post_text:
Good Afternoon Parents and Community Members,
Ensuring the safety of all our students and staff is of great importance here at Ogilvie Public Schools. We conduct many different drills throughout the year. These drills help us practice procedures so that we can act quickly and efficiently if a real situation were to occur. Today we practiced our yearly evacuation drill. You may want to take this time to discuss the procedure so that everyone stays safe.
Mrs. Suzanne Davis
Ogilvie High School Principal

post_text:
It's been a fantastic week at Ogilvie Schools with many Homecoming events. Students will participate in a pep fest later this afternoon.
Join us at the annual Dollars for Scholars Pork Chop Dinner being served in the commons from 4:30 pm to 6:30 pm.
At 5:00 pm, there's a youth football game on the football field, with the big game starting at 7:00 pm vs Onamia.
King Darius and Queen Annika, along with other Homecoming royalty, will circle the field at half time.
